snippet.textDisplay:
I made the switch from PlayStation to Xbox with the 360 and never went back. I had a PS3 for a month but then sold it on eBay. I love Xbox’s online gaming and achievement system (has added a lot of replay value to games I would’ve otherwise stopped playing... trophy system was a silly ripoff in my humble opinion). Xbox One X definitely stumbled, but GamePass is much better than anything Sony had to offer, and I got to play Resident Evil 2 which was the most important game of this generation for me.

I have great memories of PSOne and PS2, but I just don’t care about owning a PlayStation console anymore. I believe a lot of PlayStation fanboys hate on Xbox without actually ever having even played one.
snippet.textOriginal:
I made the switch from PlayStation to Xbox with the 360 and never went back. I had a PS3 for a month but then sold it on eBay. I love Xbox’s online gaming and achievement system (has added a lot of replay value to games I would’ve otherwise stopped playing...  trophy system was a silly ripoff in my humble opinion). Xbox One X definitely stumbled, but GamePass is much better than anything Sony had to offer, and I got to play Resident Evil 2 which was the most important game of this generation for me. 

I have great memories of PSOne and PS2, but I just don’t care about owning a PlayStation console anymore. I believe a lot of PlayStation fanboys hate on Xbox without actually ever having even played one.

I think this all looks great. Microsoft seems determined not to repeat their mistake in 2013 of coming to a knife fight with a sharpened stick. The OG XBONE's specs were weak as hell. Though if we're being real, both consoles were pretty limp this generation. Specs aren't everything (Nintendo is proving that in a big way) but hardware limitations put a very real limit on what can be achieved with these consoles.

Keep the fresh games coming, keep up with the backwards compatibility, don't try to shove DRM down our throats, and I can see Microsoft dominating this coming generation if they stick the landing.

With the specs they're claiming, these new systems could get pricey though.
